<title>JAPAN: Japan top banks unveil 96/97 unrealised profit.</title>
<headline>Japan top banks unveil 96/97 unrealised profit.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Japan's top 10 commercial banks on Friday disclosed their unrealised profits on securities holdings at the end of their business year on March 31.</p>
<p>Unrealised profits on securities holdings were as follows (in billions of yen unless stated, with year-ago comparisons):</p>
<p>				March 1997    March 1996</p>
<p>    Tokyo-Mitsubishi    1.60 trln     2.22 trln</p>
<p>    Sakura		  764.7	   1.60 trln</p>
<p>    Dai-Ichi Kangyo     770.5	   1.23 trln</p>
<p>    Sumitomo		688.8	   1.13 trln</p>
<p>    Fuji		    384.9	   980.5</p>
<p>    Sanwa		   719.0	   1.35 trln</p>
<p>    Tokai		   569.4	   742.4</p>
<p>    Asahi		   355.7	   881.8</p>
<p>    Daiwa		   122.4	   482.1</p>
<p>    Hokkaido Takushoku   16.9	   161.2</p>
<p>The full names of the banks are: Dai-Ichi Kangyo Bank Ltd, Sumitomo Bank Ltd, Sanwa Bank Ltd, Sakura Bank Ltd, Fuji Bank Ltd, Tokai Bank Ltd, Asahi Bank Ltd, Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi Ltd, Daiwa Bank Ltd and Hokkaido Takushoku Bank Ltd.</p>
